@startuml 02_AuthenticationFlow
participant User
participant "API Controller" as Controller
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "Database" as DB

User -> Controller: POST /auth/login\n{username, password}
activate Controller

Controller -> Auth: validateCredentials(username, password)
activate Auth

Auth -> DB: SELECT user WHERE username=?
activate DB
DB --> Auth: user record
deactivate DB

Auth -> Auth: bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
note right: Compare provided password\nwith stored hash

Auth --> Controller: {token, userId, role}
deactivate Auth

Controller --> User: 200 OK\n{token, expiresIn: 86400}
deactivate Controller

note over User: Client stores JWT token\nin Authorization header

User -> Controller: GET /projects\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>
activate Controller

Controller -> Controller: validateToken(token)
note right: Extract, verify signature,\ncheck expiration

Controller -> Auth: getUserRole(userId)\nfrom token.sub
activate Auth
Auth -> DB: SELECT role FROM users\nWHERE id=?
DB --> Auth: role
deactivate Auth
Auth --> Controller: role
deactivate Auth

Controller -> Controller: checkPermission(role, endpoint)
note right: Always re-fetch role from DB,\nnever trust token

Controller --> User: 200 OK {data}
deactivate Controller

@enduml
